Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Teburu (Japanese for â€œtableâ€) provides a web-based and mobile platform for restaurants to easily manage their online and mobile ordering services. For small to medium-sized restaurants, it's still a challenge to get the information from the ordering system to the kitchen. Typical third-party systems often forgo expensive point-of-sale (POS) integration and instead phone the restaurant, fax in orders or send orders via email. Teburu makes POS integration a more affordable option, or restaurants can opt for the company's specially designed Android tablet application which runs on locked-down mobile hardware and software. The app will alert order takers to incoming orders via flashes or beeps. Then staff simply inputs the order in their own system or prints directly to the kitchen. The overall goal is to provide SMBs with the same level of control over their menus and online ordering presence as larger companies have. The product will be white-labeled so restaurants can control own branding. A mobile app framework is also in development which would allow restaurants to take orders via a branded mobile application.

Our roots are in the Pacific Northwest, but our aspirations are global. Stohke was dreamt up over microbrews on a ski trip in Valdez, Alaska. Eric Pedersen (Founder & CEO), said to Brian Nicholson (VP of Growth & Team Manager), "why didn't we do this years ago?" It was clear, a lack of inspiration and motivation delayed their dream trip for years. They came to realize, nearly everyone they knew, lacked the necessary inspiration and motivation to live life without regrets. They promptly quit their steady jobs and set out on an insane journey to build a social platform that would inspire the world into action every day. If you're not careful, life can slowly rob you of your inspiration, motivation, health and happiness. Every day you choose where to spend your time online. Choose wisely. Stohke is here to be your primary source of inspiration and motivation each day. Stohke is the place online that inspires you to go offline. Welcome.  Stohke launched June 1st, 2017 with a couple thousand inspiring athletes, brands, causes and enthusiasts. We look forward to sharing what we've built for you.

Description: The Critical Press is a publisher of books on film and culture. Their primary focus is on short and medium-length books.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: The Critical Press is a publisher of books on film and culture. Their primary focus is on short and medium-length books: topics and arguments that can’t comfortably fit in a long article, but which can delve into a subject thoroughly and explore it accessibly in around 100 to 150 pages. Their books tackle all different aspects of film culture, form director and genre studies, to explorations of individual films, to biographies, and even topics like an oral history of video stores as told by prominent filmmakers. All of their books are available in print and ebook formats, both on their website and from major retailers and wholesalers like Amazon and Ingram.    In their first year, they have assembled a strong list of upcoming titles, and have already released three books which showcase the range of writing they will be publishing. They have spent over $70,000 of their own funds to build their list and develop their production and marketing infrastructure. However, the real challenge in the next year will be to effectively sell the many great titles they will be releasing, and funds raised will primarily be used toward hiring an experienced sales manager, developing an effective advertising strategy, and building up their boookseller contacts and resources.    They believe that this particular niche - short, smart (but not overly academic) books about film - has a strong, mature audience, and given the right tools and support the Press could be a long-lived, sustainable enterprise that can eventually yield healthy annual returns and even grow its lists to cover similar, related areas of culture (music, literature, etc.).
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment

Description: Cuyahoga Health Access Partnership is provides a coordinated system of healthcare access for the county’s low-income, uninsured adults.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Cuyahoga Health Access Partnership is provides a coordinated system of healthcare access for the county’s low-income, uninsured adults. CHAP employs trained and certified insurance navigators as a sub-grantee of the Ohio Association of Foodbanks to help connect residents to free or low-cost health insurance through Medicaid and the Health Insurance Marketplace. Although it does not offer a health insurance plan, CHAP’s first major initiative is the Access Plan for Cuyahoga County residents. This program makes it easier for uninsured adults to get the health care they need if they do not qualify for any state or federal programs. In addition to services to community residents, CHAP also serves as the convener for the Northeast Ohio Outreach & Enrollment Council.
